      "writtenOn": "2020-07-30T11:15:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Both local and on bots.  One of the biggest problems with our recipes is that they make a whole bunch of assumptions about their execution context: CWD, environment variables, expecting files to come in via isolate or CIPD and be in a specific relative location, etc, and there\u0027s no explicit declaration of these dependencies.  Moving those things into flags makes them explicit and far less error-prone.\n\nWe\u0027ll have to see how the dust settles with RBE and Niagara, but I think it\u0027d be great to move the downloading (and uploading) of CIPD and Isolate dependencies into the task driver itself, rather than relying on Swarming.\n\nIn this case, I think it\u0027s okay for the default to be \"./skia\", just as long as there\u0027s a flag to make it clear that it\u0027s something that may need to be set.",
